{
  "stem": "13469.7",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and this is really where the interrogation and all that really started, when we met the, met the Dutch authorities and the Allied Expeditionary Force, as they were called-- AEF.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, and we were medically examined and showered and cleaned and dusted and DDT sprayed and all these sort of things.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we have our registration card ticked off with all these medical situations that we had to go through.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then they wanted to know, of course, our names, where we were born.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And Eve was all right, but as soon as she came to me and [NON-ENGLISH] and they saw that we were born in Berlin, the Dutch authorities said that we were German.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we claimed that we-- the Nazis had taken the German-- and this is another thing that I forgot to mention is that another thing the Nazis did was that Jews couldn't be Germans.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So all Jews who were born in Germany were stateless.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That was one of the rules that the Nazis brought in.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we said we were stateless.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the Dutch authorities said, all those Nazi rules don't count anymore, you know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You had to wear a yellow star.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Well, we don't have to wear a yellow star anymore now.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So all these Nazi laws don't exist anymore.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the fact that they made you stateless doesn't count.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As far as we're concerned, you're German.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Germans go in camps.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So [NON-ENGLISH] and me, we were sent backward.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had our card and everything, and on the card it said we were sent to a camp in Vaals, not far from Maastricht.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were put in a camp together with Germans, including German SS officers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were in the same barracks with German SS.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
